                      U.S. 101 KEYBOARD SUPPORT


SHIFT STATUS AND INPUT MODE CHANGE KEYS


OPERATION               JAPANESE KBD            PS/2 1-1 KBD
                        (5576-A01)


Alphanumeric            Alphanumeric            Shift + Caps

Katakana                Shift + Hiragana        Alt + Caps

Hiragana                Hiragana                Ctrl + Caps

SBCS/DBCS               SBCS/DBCS               Ctrl + Back Quote

Roman/Kana Input        Alt + Hiragana          Alt + Ctrl + Caps

Kana Kanji              Alt + SBCS/DBCS         Alt + Back Quote
Conversion Mode

Kanji Code Input        Alt + Alphanumeric      Alt + Shift + Caps

Kana to Kanji           Alt + Ctrl +            Alt + Ctrl +
Control Mode            SBCS/DBCS               Back Quote



KEY ASSIGNMENTS FOR KANA KANJI CONVERSION (KKC)


OPERATION               JAPANESE KBD            PS/2 1-1 KBD
                        (5576-A01)


Conversion              Conversion              Space

No Conversion           No Conversion           Ctrl + Space

Previous Candidate      Shift + Conversion      Shift + Space

All Candidate           Alt + Conversion        Shift + Ctrl + Space

No MKK Conversion       Alt + No Conversion     Shirt + F3

Single Kanji            Ctrl + No Conversion    Ctrl + F3
Conversion



Note:  A DBCS application for PS/2 has to avoid hard coding the above
       combinations.

